                          DESIGN OUTLINE 

"Gnome Free" was the first ever adventure told in flashback, as 
Aunt Ingrid Bottomlow recounted her adventures to the Tackhammer's 
oldest daughter. The child acted as an unseen observer, commenting 
on events and providing hints (e.g if Ingrid's story was not 
progressing, saying "Auntie, hurry up and tell me the bit when you 
dug a hole and found the key"). 

The game started with Ingrid's marriage to Jasper Quickbuck and 
ended, in the worst tradition of "A Woman of Substance" epics, with 
her the richest woman in the world. 

The cover featured a barred cell door, with Ingrid visible on the 
inner sleeve through the cut-out gaps between the bars on the outer 
sleeve. If the game went badly, it turned out that Ingrid was indeed 
in prison (e.g framed by Jasper) or, if went well, that she was 
in a barred vault counting her money, or that Jasper's plots had 
rebounded and she was just visiting him. 


